            <li>
                Radha deposited ₹400 per month in a recurring deposit account for 18 months.
                The qualifying sum of money for the calculation of interest is:
                <div class="options">
                    (a) ₹ 3600<br>
                    (b) ₹ 7200<br>
                    (c) ₹ 68,400<br>
                    (d) ₹ 1,36,800
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                Find the value of 
                \[\frac{\sin \theta - 2\sin^3 \theta}{2\cos^3 \theta - \cos \theta}\]
                <div class="options">
                    (a) tan θ<br>
                    (b) cot θ<br>
                    (c) sin θ<br>
                    (d) cos θ
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                If 'a' is a natural number and one of the roots of the equation 3x² - 14x + 8 = 0, then the value of a is:
                <div class="options">
                    (a) 4<br>
                    (b) \(\frac{2}{3}\)<br>
                    (c) 8<br>
                    (d) 6
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                The mean proportion of between 9 and 16 is:
                <div class="options">
                    (a) 7<br>
                    (b) 12<br>
                    (c) 25<br>
                    (d) 144
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                Find the mean of the following observation:
                <table>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Class</th>
                        <th>Frequency</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>0-200</td>
                        <td>14</td>
                    </tr>
